# Scheduler invariants

These rules are load-bearing. Breaking any of them produces silent
correctness regressions that the test suite won't fully catch.

- **Wipe the affinity cache at the start of every `handleUserTurn`.**
  `affinityCache.clear()` is the first line. The cache is a per-turn
  optimization, not a per-session one. Carrying it across turns produces
  affinity scores from a stale prompt.
- **`pickTop3` is tiered Jaccard on course sets, not section signatures.**
  Don't reduce it to `signature(scheduleA) === signature(scheduleB)`.
  The tiers are what produce visible variety in the top-3.
- **`validateSchedule` firing means the solver produced an invalid
  schedule.** It's a solver bug, not a UI nag. Don't silence it; fix the
  generator.
- **Solver math is deterministic.** The LLM stages frame the problem
  (intent, affinity, rationale) but never decide which schedule wins.
  Anywhere a satisfaction question can be computed from the
  `RequirementGraph`, compute it; don't ask an LLM.
- See [`docs/invariants.md`](../../docs/invariants.md) and
  [`docs/architecture.md`](../../docs/architecture.md) for the full
  contract.
